## Discipline: Mandatory Behaviors

### Blast-Radius Discipline

**Before modifying any symbol**, read its impact files:

```bash
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/CALLERS.md      # who calls this — will they break?
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/REFERENCES.md   # all usage sites
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/DEPS.md         # what does this call?
```

Never modify a function signature, rename a symbol, or delete code without first understanding who depends on it. One read each — they include inline code context.

### Filter by Kind

```bash
ls file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/by-kind/fn/       # all functions
ls file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/by-kind/struct/   # all structs
ls file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/by-kind/impl/     # all impl blocks
```

## Code Relationships

**Read these sources instead of Grep for relationship queries.**

| What | Path | Use case |
|-|-|-|
| Callers (incoming) | `Foo@/CALLERS.md` | Before changing signature or behavior |
| Dependencies (outgoing) | `Foo@/DEPS.md` | Tracing what a function calls |
| All references | `Foo@/REFERENCES.md` | Before renaming, moving, or deleting |
| Definition | `Foo@/DEFINITION.md` | Where a symbol is defined |
| Declaration | `Foo@/DECLARATION.md` | Where a symbol is declared |
| Implementations | `Foo@/IMPLEMENTATION.md` | All concrete impls of a trait |

## Efficient Editing

```bash
echo 'use std::collections::HashMap;' >>file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/imports.{{ ext }} # add an import

echo 'fn process(input: &str, opts: Options) -> Result<()>' \
    >file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/signature.{{ ext }} # change signature
echo '#[instrument]' >>file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/decorators.{{ ext }} # add a decorator/attribute

rmdir file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/old_helper@/ # splices entire symbol out from source
```

## Refactoring

### Code Actions

```bash
ls file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/actions/                    # list available fixes
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/actions/10-fix.diff        # preview
patch -p1 < file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/actions/10-fix.diff   # apply

# Apply all actions for a symbol
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/actions/*.diff | patch -p1
```

## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-pattern | Correct approach |
|-|-|
| `Read file.{{ ext }}` (raw file read) | `Read file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/OVERVIEW.md` then targeted symbol |
| `Grep "fn process" src/` | `ls file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/by-kind/fn/` or `OVERVIEW.md` |
| `Grep "process" src/` for callers | `Read file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/CALLERS.md` |
| Full file read for imports | `Read file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/imports.{{ ext }}` |
| Editing raw source files | Edit `@/symbols/` bodies (tree-sitter validated) |
| Grep + manual line math for symbol | `readlink file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/at-line/42` (instant) |
| Reading N files for call sites | `CALLERS.md` has inline code context for all sites |
| Modifying without checking callers | **Always** read `CALLERS.md` first |
| Using symbol paths after a write without re-reading | Re-read `OVERVIEW.md` after writes — the symbol table may have changed |
| `Bash(cat file@/OVERVIEW.md)` for single reads | Use the **Read tool** — it's the default for all single-path `@/` reads |
| Guessing path variations on `ENOENT` | `ls symbols/` or `OVERVIEW.md` to find the current name |
| Sequential direct writes to 2+ symbols | Batch edit staging — atomic, validated |
